cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use OrbitalEdge in your research, please cite the paper below."
type: software
title: "OrbitalEdge: Cross-Layer Protocol Invariants for Proactive Handover at the LEO Satellite Edge"
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-10-01"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/hanapasandi/orbitaledge"
url: "https://hanapasandi.github.io/orbitaledge/demo/"
abstract: >
  OrbitalEdge is an O-RAN Near-RT RIC rApp for proactive LEO NTN handover prediction
  using 16 cross-layer protocol invariants spanning PHY through PDCP. A gradient-boosted
  predictor and LLM reranker (Llama-3.2-1B, LoRA fine-tuned) achieve 8.3 seconds mean
  lead time and F1 of 0.923 on a held-out carrier, improving handover-window TCP
  throughput by 34.2 percent over 3GPP Conditional Handover Release 17.

